    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. BYRNE:H.J. Res. 12.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:The constitutional authority on which this joint resolutionis based is found in Article V of the Constitution, whichgrants Congress the authority, whenever two thirds of bothchambers deem it necessary, to propose amendments to theConstitution.[Page H190]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
    <summaries>
